the nature of conflicts that are not otherwise explicitly religious. It argues that most past and present conflicts, even if the discourses about them are conducted in religious terms, have origins other than religion and/or blend religion with other causes, namely socio-economic and political injustice and inequality. Understanding the use and abuse of religion to justify violence is a prerequisite to discerning the nature of a conflict and might thus contribute to conflict resolution.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aChristianityzLatin America. 0aChristianityzMiddle East. 0aIslamzLatin America. 0aIslamzMiddle East. 0aReligion and politicszLatin America. 0aReligion and politicszMiddle East. 0aViolencexReligious aspects. 4aKonflikforschung. 4aLateinamerika. 4aNaher Osten. 4aRechtfertigung. 4aReligiöse Gewalt. 7aRELIGION / Religious Intolerance, Persecution & Conflict.2bisacsh  aConflict.  alegitimacy.  areligion.  aviolence.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2015 Part 1z978311076251808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2015z978311070098508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2015z9783110439687oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theology, Relig. Studies, Jewish Studies 2015z9783110438727oZDB-23-DGF0 cEPUBz97816145197750 cprintz978161451566140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978161451394040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781614513940423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781614513940/original  a978-3-11-070098-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2015b2015  a978-3-11-076251-8  DG Plus DeG Package 2015 Part 1b2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  